16 (A) A property owner desiring the benefit of such methods of assessment and
17 taxation shall be required to enter into a covenant to continue the property in bona fide
18 conservation use or bona fide residential transitional use; and
19 (B) A breach of such covenant within ten years shall result in a recapture of the tax
20 savings resulting from such methods of assessment and taxation and may result in other
21 appropriate penalties; and"
22 SECTION 2.
23 The above proposed amendment to the Constitution shall be published and submitted as
24 provided in Article X, Section I, Paragraph II of the Constitution. The ballot submitting the
25 above proposed amendment shall have written or printed thereon the following:
26 "( ) YES Shall the Constitution of Georgia, for the purpose of protecting family
27 ( ) NO farmland, be amended so as to increase the maximum acreage to qualify for
28 assessment and taxation as a bona fide conservation use property from 2,000
29 acres to 4,000 acres?"
30 All persons desiring to vote in favor of ratifying the proposed amendment shall vote "Yes."
31 All persons desiring to vote against ratifying the proposed amendment shall vote "No." If
32 such amendment shall be ratified as provided in said Paragraph of the Constitution, it shall
33 become a part of the Constitution of this state.
